Sentencas: NiO-YSZ anode supports with different microstructures have been successfully prepared through a phase-inversion method.
Titulo: Effects on microstructure of NiO-YSZ anode support fabricated by phase-inversion method

Sentencas: The effect of non-solvent, precipitation time and polyethersulfone (PESf) concentration on the microstructure development of NiO-YSZ anode support has been investigated.
Titulo: Effects on microstructure of NiO-YSZ anode support fabricated by phase-inversion method

Sentencas: The scanning electron microscopy (SEM) results of NiO-YSZ anode support show that four types of microstructures have been achieved using different non-solvent.
Titulo: Effects on microstructure of NiO-YSZ anode support fabricated by phase-inversion method

Sentencas: The difference in solubility parameters between solvent and non-solvent can greatly influence the microstructure.
Titulo: Effects on microstructure of NiO-YSZ anode support fabricated by phase-inversion method

Sentencas: Further, it is observed that the precipitation time will affect the formation of macro-voids in the anode support, and higher PESf concentration in the slurry will suppress the formation of macro-voids.
Titulo: Effects on microstructure of NiO-YSZ anode support fabricated by phase-inversion method

Sentencas: In addition, planar NiO-YSZ anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with four types of anode microstructures have been fabricated and tested.
Titulo: Effects on microstructure of NiO-YSZ anode support fabricated by phase-inversion method

Sentencas: The correlation between the electrochemical performance of all the prepared anode materials and microstructure of these cells has been discussed.
Titulo: Effects on microstructure of NiO-YSZ anode support fabricated by phase-inversion method
